sentences: Rowland Constantine O'Malley Armstrong (born 8 May 1966) is an English music producer and multi-instrumentalist.

Armstrong has appeared on a large number of music projects, both within groups and solo, using various monikers, including Faithless (which he formed in 1995 with Sister Bliss, Jamie Catto and Maxi Jazz), Rollo Goes ..., Our Tribe (with Rob Dougan), and Dusted.
In late 1991, Armstrong founded Cheeky Records, releasing two singles before the label folded.
In 1992 Champion Records stepped in to help with funding and advice, and the label was restarted, with Reverence by Faithless its first album release (it has since been bought out by BMG).

In 1992, Armstrong co-wrote and co-produced Felix's hit single "Don't You Want Me", which reached number 1 in Finland, Italy, Spain and Switzerland, as well as reaching number 6 on the UK Singles Chart.
Armstrong composed the official melody of the UEFA Euro 2008 and UEFA Euro 2012.
Armstrong composed the official melody of the UEFA Euro 2008 and UEFA Euro 2012.
He was nominated for an Academy Award in the category of Best Original Song for his work with A.R. Rahman and Dido on "If I Rise", featuring in the 2010 Danny Boyle film 127 Hours.

In July 2021, Armstrong (as the alias R Plus) released “Hey Lover” which featured singer Amelia Fox.
The pair had previously collaborated on a cover of Joy Division’s 1980 hit “Love Will Tear Us Apart” which Armstrong released in May 2021.
